\".join(sys.stdin.readlines())\nhtml = conv.convert(ansi)\n```\n\n## Example - Shell Usage\n\n```shell\n$ ls --color=always | ansi2html > directories.html\n$ sudo tail /var/log/messages | ccze -A | ansi2html > logs.html\n$ task rc._forcecolor:yes limit:0 burndown | ansi2html > burndown.html\n```\n\nSee the list of full options with:\n\n```shell\n$ ansi2html --help\n```\n\n## Get this project:\n\n```shell\n$ pip3 install ansi2html\n```\n\nSource: <https://github.com/pycontribs/ansi2html/>\n\npypi: <https://pypi.org/project/ansi2html/>\n\n## License\n\n`ansi2html` is licensed LGPLv3+.\n\n# Credits\n\n- Author: [Ralph Bean](mailto:rbean@redhat.com)\n- Contributor: [Robin Schneider](mailto:ypid23@aol.de)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ansi2html.util", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ansi2html.util.read_to_unicode", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "BinaryIO", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.BinaryIO", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ansi2html", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "ansi2html.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ansi2html.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "ansi2html.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "ansi2html._version.__version__", "project": null}}, {"name": "ansi2html.Ansi2HTMLConverter", "xref": {"fqname": "ansi2html.converter.Ansi2HTMLConverter", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "ansi2html.converter", "documentation": ["encoding: utf-8", "This file is part of ansi2html", "Convert ANSI (terminal) colours and attributes to HTML", "Copyright (C) 2012  Ralph Bean <rbean@redhat.com>", "Copyright (C) 2013  Sebastian Pipping <sebast